Alaska & New Adventures
Back in May, I took an amazing trip with Brandon to Alaska🌊🌲🫎🤍
I needed it.  Kind and cheerful people, breathtaking nature, the freshest air.  It gave me a chance breathe out the old and in with the new💙
Once we were home I started my voice acting journey, assisted directed on a film to prepare myself for my turn at the wheel.  We wrapped Wayward, a horror/drama short I performed in and helped produce.  A beautiful story which had one of the hardest scenes I’ve ever done.  I couldn’t have asked for better people to do it with.
I can call myself an actor, writer, and producer now and✨ I’m going to do so much more.✨ The hard work feels good!  The past few months have been nothing short of invigorating and it’s the people I’m surrounded by that inspired me and made this possible.
This is your reminder to try new things.  Give yourself a chance and you will surprise yourself!  And get surrounded by people who believe in the dream.
